(1)

1041 Elmore Place, (East 22nd Street), east side, between Aves. I. & J., showing the Robert Magaw farmhouse, built in 1725 originally located on the west side of Ocean Ave., near East 21st Street, facing south. Col. Robert Magaw, born 1752 in Ireland; in 1779 he married Martitie Van Brunt. Their son, Van Brunt Magaw, (1783-1831) married Adrianne Voorhees of Flatbush in 1811. Robert Magaw, (1817-1887), the 3rd son of Van Brunt Magaw, was a farmer at Flatlands. Van Brunt Magaw, born 1844, worked the farm until about 1895. In 1915 the house was owned by George H. Henderson.

May 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster collection.

(2)

The same, from another angle.

May 1923.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)

The same, from another angle.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
